    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p><strong>Warden-Sergeant Eirik Greyhand</strong> commands the Chainwarden Toll at Greypass&mdash;a fortified checkpoint in the Midgard's Shield foothills. He is not corrupt, just exhausted. The toll is underfunded, understaffed, and overwhelmed by refugees.</p><p>Eirik wants order. He wants the fiction that the system works. He desperately needs supplies&mdash;fuel and rations are worth more than coin. He has a family in Hrafnborg and hasn't heard from them in a month; any news is worth something to him.</p><p>Those who watch him carefully may notice a stillness when Root-language words or Keeper references are spoken nearby &mdash; a pause, a slight turn of the head, gone faster than thought. He does not speak of it. He has not spoken of certain things in a very long time.</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
